{id:'q4_s_001',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'medium',year:2022,topic:'Space Milestones',
q:'India\'s Mangalyaan (MOM) mission was historic because:',
opts:['First mission to land on Mars','First Mars mission to succeed on maiden attempt — India became 4th space agency to reach Mars at a cost of only $74 million','India\'s first satellite mission','A crewed mission to Mars orbit'],
ans:1,
explain:'Mangalyaan (September 24, 2014): India became 4th space agency (after USSR, NASA, ESA) to reach Mars. First in world to succeed on maiden attempt. Cost $74 million — less than some Hollywood films.',
wrongExplain:'Chandrayaan-1 = lunar (2008). Mangalyaan = Mars (2013). Aditya-L1 = Sun (2023). Gaganyaan = crewed spaceflight (upcoming). Mangalyaan operated 8+ years vs 6-month design life.'},

{id:'q4_s_002',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'LVM3',
q:'India\'s LVM3 (Launch Vehicle Mark 3) is significant as:',
opts:['India\'s smallest satellite launcher','India\'s heaviest rocket — 4-tonne to GTO capacity — used for Chandrayaan-3 and OneWeb commercial launches','Only for lunar missions','Only for government satellites'],
ans:1,
explain:'LVM3 (formerly GSLV Mk III): India\'s most powerful rocket. 4T to GTO or 10T to LEO. Cryogenic upper stage (C25) is indigenous breakthrough. Used for Chandrayaan-2, Chandrayaan-3, OneWeb commercial launches.',
wrongExplain:'PSLV = reliable workhorse (25 kg to 1.75T). LVM3 = heavy-lift. SSLV = small satellite (500 kg). IN-SPACe now allows private sector (Agnikul, Skyroot) to use Indian launch facilities.'},

{id:'q4_s_003',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'medium',year:2021,topic:'Quantum Computing',
q:'Quantum computing differs from classical computing primarily because:',
opts:['It is faster for all types of tasks','It uses qubits that can be 0 and 1 simultaneously (superposition) enabling exponential parallelism for specific problems like cryptography and optimization','It requires less electricity','It works without any physical hardware'],
ans:1,
explain:'Quantum computing: Qubits exploit superposition + entanglement. Exponentially more computational states. Extremely powerful for: breaking encryption, drug discovery, materials science, financial optimization.',
wrongExplain:'Classical computers use bits (0 or 1). Google Sycamore (2019) claimed quantum supremacy. India\'s National Quantum Mission (2023): Rs 6,000 crore, 8-year mission for 50-1000 qubit systems.'},

{id:'q4_s_004',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'hard',year:2022,topic:'LLMs',
q:'Large Language Models (LLMs) like GPT generate text by:',
opts:['Copying text stored in a database','Predicting the most probable next token based on context — using transformer architecture trained on massive text datasets to learn statistical patterns','Rule-based text template selection','Only translating between languages'],
ans:1,
explain:'LLMs: Trained on enormous text datasets. At inference, predict next token probabilistically given context. Emergent abilities (reasoning, coding, translation) arise at scale. Hallucination = generates plausible but false content.',
wrongExplain:'Transformer architecture (2017, Google: "Attention is All You Need"). Self-attention mechanism. India\'s AI policy under IndiaAI Mission 2024. DPDP Act 2023 relevant for AI data use.'},

{id:'q4_s_005',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'medium',year:2020,topic:'Bt Cotton',
q:'Bt Cotton in India involves:',
opts:['Special chemical treatment of cotton seeds','Insertion of Cry gene from Bacillus thuringiensis bacterium — makes cotton plants produce proteins toxic to bollworm (Helicoverpa armigera)','Hybrid seed technology only, no genetic modification','An organic farming technique'],
ans:1,
explain:'Bt Cotton: GM cotton approved in India 2002. Contains Cry1Ac + Cry2Ab genes. Reduced pesticide use by ~40-50% for bollworm. India is now world\'s largest cotton producer. Over 95% of cotton area uses Bt varieties.',
wrongExplain:'Bt Brinjal: Government moratorium (2010) despite GEAC approval. GM food crops: not approved commercially in India. Bt Cotton = only approved GM food crop (technically non-food). Regulatory debate continues.'},

{id:'q4_s_006',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'Biodiversity Act',
q:'People\'s Biodiversity Registers (PBR) under Biological Diversity Act 2002:',
opts:['Only document Protected Area boundaries','Document local biological resources, cultivation knowledge, and traditional uses at panchayat level — first line of defense against biopiracy','Only corporate biodiversity patents','Scientific research findings exclusively'],
ans:1,
explain:'PBRs: Panchayat-level documentation by Biodiversity Management Committees. Records: local species, traditional uses, cultivation knowledge. Enables ABS (Access and Benefit Sharing) when outsiders want to use this knowledge.',
wrongExplain:'National Biodiversity Authority (Chennai) oversees. State Biodiversity Boards. BMCs at local level maintain PBRs. India\'s fight against Neem/turmeric patents used this documentation framework.'},

{id:'q4_s_007',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s4',difficulty:'medium',year:2021,topic:'Zero Day',
q:'A "Zero-Day Vulnerability" in cybersecurity means:',
opts:['An old 1990s software bug finally discovered','A software flaw unknown to the vendor being actively exploited by attackers — zero days available for the defender to patch','A server that has been offline for zero days','Standard software maintenance issue'],
ans:1,
explain:'Zero-Day: Software vulnerability unknown to vendor. Attackers exploit it before patch is developed and deployed. Extremely valuable in cyberwarfare. Pegasus spyware used zero-days in WhatsApp and iOS.',
wrongExplain:'Pegasus (NSO Group, Israel): Exploited zero-days for covert phone surveillance. India investigated after journalists/activists were targeted. CERT-In handles national cybersecurity incidents.'},

{id:'q4_s_008',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s4',difficulty:'hard',year:2022,topic:'E2E Encryption',
q:'End-to-End Encryption (E2EE) ensures:',
opts:['Server provider can decrypt messages for security screening','Only the sender and recipient can read messages — platform operator, government, and ISPs cannot access the content','Government can always access with a court order','Only used for video calls, not text'],
ans:1,
explain:'E2EE: Messages encrypted on sender\'s device, decrypted only on recipient\'s device. WhatsApp, Signal, iMessage use E2EE. Middle parties cannot read content. Protects privacy but complicates law enforcement.',
wrongExplain:'India\'s proposed IT Rules on traceability: identifying first originator of viral messages would require breaking E2EE. Conflicts with Puttaswamy (Right to Privacy). SC is examining this tension.'},

{id:'q4_s_009',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'medium',year:2020,topic:'ISS',
q:'The International Space Station (ISS) orbits Earth at approximately:',
opts:['100 km altitude (edge of space)','400-420 km altitude (Low Earth Orbit) — completing one orbit every ~92 minutes at 27,600 km/h','1,000 km altitude','35,786 km (geostationary orbit)'],
ans:1,
explain:'ISS: ~400 km altitude, ~92-minute orbit period, speed ~7.7 km/s. Crew of 6-7. ISS life extended to 2030. India is in discussions for participation. Will be deorbited into Pacific Ocean after 2030.',
wrongExplain:'Geostationary orbit = 35,786 km (INSAT, GSAT communication satellites). Sun-synchronous orbit = ~500-600 km (Cartosat, Resourcesat Earth observation). ISS = LEO.'},

{id:'q4_s_010',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'medium',year:2023,topic:'National Quantum Mission',
q:'India\'s National Quantum Mission (NQM) 2023 targets:',
opts:['Import quantum computers from USA','Develop intermediate-scale quantum computers (50-1000 qubits), quantum communications, atomic clocks — Rs 6,000 crore, 8-year mission','Only theoretical quantum research','Only quantum encryption for defence'],
ans:1,
explain:'NQM 2023-2031: Rs 6,000 crore. Four Thematic Hubs: quantum computing, quantum communication, quantum sensing/metrology, quantum materials. First phase: 50-qubit computers by 2028.',
wrongExplain:'Global quantum race: USA (IBM Osprey 433 qubits), China, EU. India catching up. Applications: drug discovery, materials, cryptography, navigation, weather modeling.'},

{id:'q4_s_011',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'hard',year:2021,topic:'CAR-T Therapy',
q:'CAR-T Cell Therapy for cancer involves:',
opts:['A new generation chemotherapy drug injection','Patient\'s own T-cells extracted, genetically engineered to target specific cancer cell antigens, multiplied and reinfused — a living personalized drug','Improved radiation therapy using proton beams','Immunosuppression to prevent cancer spread'],
ans:1,
explain:'CAR-T (Chimeric Antigen Receptor T-cell): Effective for blood cancers (ALL, multiple myeloma, large B-cell lymphoma). India\'s NexCAR19 (IIT Bombay/ICI) = first indigenous CAR-T approved 2024. Cost: ~Rs 30 lakh vs $4 million in USA.',
wrongExplain:'India\'s NexCAR19 is a global milestone — made CAR-T therapy accessible for middle-income countries. Earlier treatments cost prohibitively in USA. India\'s pharma sector developing this as a scalable product.'},

{id:'q4_s_012',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'medium',year:2019,topic:'NavIC',
q:'NavIC (Navigation with Indian Constellation) provides India with:',
opts:['Internet connectivity to rural areas','Independent navigation capability (like GPS) covering India + 1500 km surrounding region — strategic autonomy post-Kargil War lesson','Weather forecasting only','Only maritime navigation'],
ans:1,
explain:'NavIC (IRNSS): 7 satellites. Coverage: India + 1,500 km surrounding region. Accuracy: <20m (civil), <10m (restricted). Kargil War (1999): USA denied precision GPS data — motivated India to build own system.',
wrongExplain:'NavIC vs GPS: GPS = global (USA), NavIC = regional (India). NavIC essential for: fishing boats (SMS alerts), vehicle navigation, defence precision strike, disaster management. ISRO developing NavIC chips for mobile phones.'},

{id:'q4_s_013',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s4',difficulty:'medium',year:2022,topic:'CBDC vs UPI',
q:'Digital Rupee (CBDC) differs from UPI because:',
opts:['They are identical, just different names','UPI is payment infrastructure moving existing bank money between accounts; Digital Rupee is a form of money itself — a direct liability of RBI, like cash but digital','Digital Rupee is a cryptocurrency','UPI is more secure than Digital Rupee'],
ans:1,
explain:'UPI: Rails for transferring commercial bank money. Digital Rupee (e₹): Is the money itself — RBI\'s direct liability. Can work offline, no bank account needed. Two types: e₹-W (wholesale interbank), e₹-R (retail public).',
wrongExplain:'UPI transaction = your bank account balance moves. e₹ transaction = the digital currency itself moves. e₹ can be programmed (e.g., only usable for specific purposes). Financial inclusion potential is higher.'},

{id:'q4_s_014',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'AI Governance',
q:'India\'s approach to AI regulation includes:',
opts:['Complete ban on AI development','IndiaAI Mission 2024 (Rs 10,000 crore for AI infrastructure) + DPDP Act 2023 for data privacy + proposed AI advisory/safety framework — enabling innovation with guardrails','No regulation whatsoever','Mandatory government approval for every AI application'],
ans:1,
explain:'IndiaAI Mission (2024): Rs 10,000 crore for compute infrastructure, dataset platform, India-specific AI models, AI in governance. DPDP Act provides data governance. India aims to be a global AI hub.',
wrongExplain:'India\'s AI strategy: sovereign AI capability + safety framework. Contrasts with EU AI Act (comprehensive regulation) and US Executive Order (risk-based). India balances innovation with safety.'},

{id:'q4_s_015',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'medium',year:2021,topic:'Precision Agriculture',
q:'Precision Agriculture combines:',
opts:['Only traditional farming techniques with modern seeds','GPS/GNSS + IoT sensors + satellite imagery + drones + big data analytics — to optimize inputs (water, fertilizer, pesticide) field by field','Only drone usage in farming','Only weather monitoring'],
ans:1,
explain:'Precision Agriculture: Data-driven farming. GPS-guided tractors, IoT soil sensors, satellite NDVI imaging (crop health), drone spraying. Apply right inputs, right place, right time. Reduces input costs, increases yield.',
wrongExplain:'India\'s AgriStack (digital public infrastructure for agriculture), ISRO satellite data for crop insurance, PM Kisan Drones scheme. With 150 million farm holdings, precision ag potential is enormous but adoption is slow.'},

{id:'q4_s_016',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'hard',year:2022,topic:'Solar Sails',
q:'Solar Sail technology for spacecraft propulsion uses:',
opts:['Nuclear energy from onboard reactor','Radiation pressure of sunlight on large reflective sail — photons exert tiny but continuous force, no fuel required','Magnetic field interaction with solar wind','Microwave beaming from Earth'],
ans:1,
explain:'Solar Sails: Photons have momentum — when they reflect off large mirror-like sail, they transfer momentum. Small but continuous force over months = significant acceleration. IKAROS (Japan 2010) = first successful solar sail.',
wrongExplain:'Advantages: no propellant (sunlight is free and continuous), years of acceleration. Disadvantages: very slow initially, doesn\'t work far from Sun. Future concept: interstellar sail to Alpha Centauri (Breakthrough Starshot).'},

{id:'q4_s_017',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s4',difficulty:'medium',year:2020,topic:'Dark Web',
q:'The "Dark Web" refers to:',
opts:['Poorly connected internet in rural areas','Encrypted overlay networks (like Tor) accessible only with special software — used for both legitimate privacy and illegal activities','Government classified intranet networks','Low-quality poorly designed websites'],
ans:1,
explain:'Dark Web: Content on Tor (The Onion Router) or I2P networks. Traffic routed through multiple servers for anonymity. Legitimate uses: journalists in authoritarian states, whistleblowers. Illegal: drug markets, stolen data, weapons.',
wrongExplain:'Deep Web = any content not indexed by search engines (email, banking, research databases). Dark Web ⊂ Deep Web. Most Dark Web is mundane — media overstates criminal use. Tor was created by US Naval Research Laboratory.'},

{id:'q4_s_018',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'mRNA Platform',
q:'mRNA technology beyond COVID vaccines is being applied to:',
opts:['Only COVID vaccines permanently','Personalized cancer vaccines (targeting individual tumor mutations) + protein replacement therapy for rare diseases + HIV vaccines in clinical trials','General antibiotics production','Standard diagnostic testing'],
ans:1,
explain:'mRNA platform: Rapidly programmable for any protein target. Cancer vaccines: sequence tumor DNA, identify mutations, design mRNA to train immune system against that patient\'s specific cancer. Moderna/BioNTech in trials.',
wrongExplain:'mRNA degrades quickly (doesn\'t permanently alter DNA). The same manufacturing platform can pivot to new diseases rapidly. mRNA is likely the most impactful medical technology platform of the 21st century.'},

{id:'q4_s_019',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'medium',year:2021,topic:'Optical Fiber',
q:'Optical Fiber communication uses:',
opts:['Electrical signals in copper wire','Pulses of light through glass/plastic fiber — much higher bandwidth, negligible signal loss, immune to electromagnetic interference compared to copper cable','Radio waves through vacuum','Satellite microwave relay systems'],
ans:1,
explain:'Optical Fiber: Data = light pulses through total internal reflection. Bandwidth: 100+ Tbps per fiber. BharatNet: fiber to all gram panchayats. India\'s 5G backhaul uses optical fiber.',
wrongExplain:'5G uses optical fiber for backhaul (connection between towers) + radio waves for last-mile access. GPON (Gigabit Passive Optical Network) = standard for fiber-to-home. India\'s fiber penetration key for digital economy.'},

{id:'q4_s_020',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'medium',year:2022,topic:'RISAT',
q:'India\'s RISAT (Radar Imaging Satellite) series is used for:',
opts:['Communication services','All-weather, day-night synthetic aperture radar (SAR) imaging — critical for border surveillance, flood mapping, cyclone tracking, crop assessment','Navigation (NavIC)','Weather forecasting only'],
ans:1,
explain:'RISAT: SAR-based. Unlike optical imaging, SAR works through clouds and at night. RISAT-2BR uses X-band for high-resolution imaging. Used for: China border monitoring, disaster management, agricultural assessment.',
wrongExplain:'Cartosat = optical imaging for topography. ResourceSat = land use and agriculture (optical). OceanSat = ocean color and wind. INSAT/GSAT = communication. RISAT = all-weather radar.'},

{id:'q4_s_021',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'medium',year:2020,topic:'AMR',
q:'Antimicrobial Resistance (AMR) is described as a major crisis because:',
opts:['Antibiotics are becoming too expensive for patients','Bacteria evolve resistance faster than new antibiotics are developed — WHO projects 10 million deaths/year by 2050 from drug-resistant infections','Antibiotics cause severe side effects','Manufacturing capacity is insufficient'],
ans:1,
explain:'AMR: Overuse in humans + livestock → resistant bacteria evolve and spread. India = high AMR burden due to easy antibiotic availability, self-medication, agricultural use. Last-resort antibiotics (colistin, carbapenems) showing resistance.',
wrongExplain:'India\'s National Action Plan on AMR (2017). Red Line Campaign: prescription-only for antibiotics showing red line on packaging. WHO Global Action Plan. AMR is called the "silent pandemic."'},

{id:'q4_s_022',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s4',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'IT Act S66A',
q:'Section 66A of IT Act was struck down by the Supreme Court in 2015 because:',
opts:['It was too lenient on cybercrime','In Shreya Singhal v. UoI — it criminalized "offensive" online speech with vague undefined terms, creating chilling effect on free speech under Art 19(1)(a)','It was never properly enacted by Parliament','It duplicated IPC provisions'},
ans:1,
explain:'Section 66A: Imprisonment for posting "grossly offensive" or "menacing" content online. SC found: terms like "grossly offensive" undefined, overbroad, chilling effect. Struck down unanimously.',
wrongExplain:'Section 69A still stands = website blocking on national security grounds. Puttaswamy (2017) further strengthened digital rights. Shreya Singhal = landmark internet freedom case in India.'},

{id:'q4_s_023',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s1',difficulty:'medium',year:2021,topic:'Tejas LCA',
q:'HAL Tejas LCA is significant because:',
opts:['India\'s first fighter aircraft ever','India\'s first indigenously developed single-engine multirole combat aircraft — marks milestone in defense self-reliance (Atmanirbhar Bharat in defence)','Purchased from France under Make in India','Only used as a trainer aircraft'],
ans:1,
explain:'Tejas: Developed by HAL + ADA (Aeronautical Development Agency). Delta wing, fly-by-wire, composite airframe. Inducted into IAF. Mk1A (advanced version) on order. India reducing dependence on foreign fighter imports.',
wrongExplain:'AMCA (Advanced Medium Combat Aircraft) = India\'s stealth 5th-gen fighter under development. LCA Mk2 = improved Tejas. DRDO, HAL, private sector all involved. India aspires to become major defence exporter.'},

{id:'q4_s_024',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s2',difficulty:'medium',year:2022,topic:'Blockchain',
q:'Blockchain technology\'s core innovation is:',
opts:['A centralized database with better security','Distributed immutable ledger — transactions in cryptographically chained blocks, verified by network consensus, no single authority can alter records','Faster internet protocol for payments','Better data encryption algorithm only'],
ans:1,
explain:'Blockchain: Each block contains transaction data + hash of previous block. Changing any block invalidates all subsequent blocks. Network consensus validates transactions. Transparency + immutability without central authority.',
wrongExplain:'Applications: cryptocurrency, supply chain, land records, healthcare. India\'s blockchain: NeSL (legal documents), GSTN exploring blockchain, RBI\'s CBDC uses DLT (related technology). Not only for crypto.'},

{id:'q4_s_025',subject:'Sci & Tech',node:'s3',difficulty:'hard',year:2023,topic:'Biopharma',
q:'India\'s National Biopharma Mission (Innovate in India — i3) aims to:',
opts:['Only regulate foreign pharmaceutical companies in India','Build end-to-end biopharmaceutical innovation ecosystem: vaccines, biosimilars, biologics, diagnostics — moving India beyond generic drugs to innovative biologics','Import all high-value medicines','Only control drug prices through NPPA'],
ans:1,
explain:'National Biopharma Mission: Rs 1,500 crore. India = "Pharmacy of the World" for generics. Mission aims for: innovative biologics (not just biosimilars), mAbs, cell/gene therapies, vaccines. Serum Institute + new startups.',
wrongExplain:'India supplies 60% of global vaccines, 20% of generic drugs. But mostly low-margin generics. i3 Mission + BIRAC funding + Genome India Project = India\'s push into innovative biologics.'},

